Peste des petits ruminants, China
---------------------------------
Information received on [and dated] 2 Jan 2014 from Dr Zhang Zhongqui, Director General, China Animal Disease Control Centre, Veterinary Bureau, Ministry of Agriculture, Beijing, China (People's Rep. of)

Summary
Report type: follow-up report No. 2
Date of start of the event: 5 Dec 2013
Date of pre-confirmation of the event: 5 Dec 2013
Report date: 2 Jan 2014
Date submitted to OIE: 2 Jan 2014
Reason for notification: 1st occurrence of a listed disease
Manifestation of disease: clinical disease
Causal agent: peste des petits ruminants virus
Nature of diagnosis: suspicion, clinical, laboratory (basic), laboratory (advanced)
This event pertains to a defined within the country

New outbreaks (1)
Summary of outbreaks
Total outbreaks: 1

Outbreak 1: Sayibage Village, Luntai, Bayinggol Mongolia Autonomous Prefecture, Xinjiang
Date of start of the outbreak: 29 Dec 2013
Outbreak status: continuing (or date resolved not provided)
Epidemiological unit: farm
Affected animals:
Species / Susceptible / Cases / Deaths / Destroyed / Slaughtered
Sheep / Goats / 203 / 160 / 38 / 165 / 0
Outbreak statistics:
Species / Apparent morbidity rate / Apparent mortality rate / Apparent case fatality rate / Proportion susceptible animals lost*
Sheep / Goats / 78.82 percent / 18.72 percent / 23.75 percent / 100 percent
*Removed from the susceptible population through death, destruction, and/or slaughter

Epidemiology
Source of the outbreak(s) or origin of infection: unknown or inconclusive

Control measures
Measures applied: stamping out; quarantine; movement control inside the country; screening; zoning; disinfection of infected premises/establishment(s); dipping/spraying; no vaccination; no treatment of affected animals
Measures to be applied: no other measures

Diagnostic test results
Laboratory name and type / Species / Test / Test date / Result
National Research Center for Exotic Animal Diseases (national laboratory) / sheep-goats / enzyme-linked immunosorbent assay (ELISA) / 2 Jan 2014 / Positive
National Research Center for Exotic Animal Diseases (national laboratory) / sheep-goats / reverse transcription-polymerase chain reaction (PCR) / 2 Jan 2014 / Positive

Future reporting
The event is continuing. Weekly follow-up reports will be submitted.

The location of the outbreak can be seen on the interactive map included in the OIE report at the source URL above.

